      "text": "Alcohol deserves its own note because it's the single most common setting for a slip. Two reasons. First, drinking lowers your guard and quiets the rational mind that knows the trap — \"just one won't hurt\" sounds far more reasonable after a couple of drinks. Second, drinking and smoking were probably paired hundreds of times, so the cue is intense. This combination undoes more quits than almost anything else.\n\nYou don't necessarily have to avoid alcohol — but for the first couple of weeks, go in with your eyes open and your decision pre-made. Decide before the first drink, while completely clear-headed, that there is no scenario tonight in which you take a puff. Don't leave it to in-the-moment judgement, because in-the-moment judgement is exactly what alcohol erodes. A pre-made, sober decision holds when a tipsy one wouldn't."
